{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "17", "m": "07", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "07", "M": "49", "S": "20"}}, "news": [{"title": "Civic body sets up tax camps as Panchkula property tax recovery lags", "para": "Panchkula Municipal Corporation is organizing property tax camps to assist residents with dues.  These camps aim to help defaulters clear outstanding amounts before the extended August 31 deadline.  A 75% interest waiver is available on arrears if paid by August 31, 2026.  Over 60% of properties have not yet completed self-certification for tax purposes.  Failure to comply may lead to recovery proceedings and legal action against property owners.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/panchkula-launches-property-tax-camps-amid-collection-shortfalls/132455457?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-1461366/132455457.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Upgradation, allotment of over 7,400 EWS flats at Bhalswa being expedited: Delhi minister", "para": "Delhi Urban Development Minister Ashish Sood announced the expedited upgradation of over 7,400 EWS flats.  Existing flats are being expanded to improve living conditions for beneficiaries.  The government plans phased allotment after completing the repair and expansion work.  This initiative aims to provide dignified housing for economically weaker families.  The project budget has significantly increased under the current administration.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/delhi-government-accelerates-allotment-of-7400-ews-flats-at-bhalswa/132455560?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-2071122/132455560.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "Ranchi cracks down on illegal rural construction", "para": "Ranchi administration warns property owners about illegal rural construction. Mandatory building plan approvals are required for constructions over 5,000 square feet. The Zila Parishad now handles layout plan approvals for rural areas. Owners must submit digital applications through registered architects for transparency. Failure to comply risks legal action and demolition liabilities.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/ranchi-government-to-enforce-strict-measures-against-illegal-rural-construction/132455391?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-1618462/132455391.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}]}